Description: Bracken Construction provides crane and steel erection services, along with heavy hauling services, that lead the industry.
Full Description: Bracken Construction Company began when three partners moved their newly created crane and steel erection business to a service station on South Gallatin Street in Jackson, Mississippi, in 1956. The brothers Ray and C.P., the company's founding partners, guided the company's growth in this location. Until 1962, Bracken and John Shivers worked together. During that year, Bracken Construction Company moved to 5068 Gault Street, where it remained for 23 years. J.C., another brother, was born that same year. When Bracken purchased the interest of John Shivers, he joined the company. Bracken Construction Company owned eight cranes by 1966. After purchasing its first hydraulic crane, a 25-ton Warner & Swaysey model in 1969, the company would continue to add many more to its inventory over the next few decades. After C.P. Bracken died in 1975, his remaining two partners continued to grow and expand the business. A core of hardworking, experienced ironworkers and crane operators helped Bracken win the loyalty of its customers and employees.

Full Description: Zona, Inc., delivers a complete network solution to support Massive Multi-Player Online Games (MMOG) throughout the entire product development cycle of a game -- from conception, all the way through the full life of a game. Founded in August 2000, the company is applying their unique solution called Terazona(R) to support tens of thousands of simultaneous MMOG players in a seamless, fault-tolerant universe of gameplay. Unlike many legacy systems of today, Terazona(R) will allow developers to focus more resources on game design to enhance player experience, spend less time and money on server and infrastructure issues, and significantly shorten a game's time to market. Zona, Inc., is a privately held company based in Redwood City. In addition to the U.S., the company is actively introducing their complete solution for MMOG to Taiwan, China, Korea and Japan through Zona's foreign offices. Zona, Inc., also has secured Tools & Middleware licenses from Microsoft's Xbox and Sony Computer Entertainment Inc.'s PlayStation(R) 2.
